{
  "stem": "14168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first job that I got in Bolivia was translator, interpreter, for the Bolivian army, which I thought would pay my bills.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It didn't, because after four weeks, I found out that they told me that they had not any-- they did not have any budgetary appropriations for the job.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I worked for nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then I opened up a translator bureau in Bolivia, which was all right.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I helped-- I also translated and interpreted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I helped the Jewish community, because sometimes immigrants got into legal difficulties, and I was able to interpret for them and help them out their difficulties.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I knew some Bolivian officials, so that worked out all right.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But then later on, I got employed by a British firm again, import/export.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then things got very, very tough, politically.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Bolivia was a country of great interest to the Axis powers because it had a lot of raw materials, tin and everything else.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were very friendly-- the government people-- towards Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Germans had been there 100 years before, and they liked the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were a little bit anti-American-- imperialism and what have you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they were fertile ground for Nazi infiltrators and Nazi agents who were trying to create little problems for the Americans to divert their attention.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After 1940, a group formed of Jewish people, and also non-Jews, who had fled Germany, to fight the German influence in Bolivia, and to also try to expose the German embassy in Bolivia as the center of Nazi espionage.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were able to do that, because the postmaster who was in Bolivia, La Paz, was on our side and a little bit of a, shall we say, realistic remuneration for his services was available.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
